Reality TV star, Queen Mercy Atang has expressed her opinion on the debate over ladies insisting on getting fare from men after a date. Some celebrities have argued it was a man’s responsibility to give fare to a woman while on a date. The topic has continued to gather reactions with some arguing for and others against. Queen however has advised her female fans otherwise. Read Also: I’ll marry any man that sends me fuel-Waje   Fuel scarcity: Victoria Kolawole frustrated as fan bolts…     I’ll marry any man that sends me fuel-Waje     It is my choice to be a second wife, Mercy Aigbe tells…   According to the former BBNaija season 6 housemate, asking a man for transport fare is embarrassing same way a woman will find it ridiculous when a man requests for same. Atang noted the only basis on which a woman can request transport fare from a man is if they have a good rapport and very much familiar with each other. She wrote: “MY GIRLS, TRANSPORT FARE SHOULD NEVER BE A PROBLEM. IT’S EVEN AN EMBARRASSING TO ASK… “IF A GUY COMES VISITING AND REQUESTS TRANSPORT FARE, YOU KNOW HOW RIDICULOUS IT WOULD SEEM. YOU’LL EVEN GIST YOUR GIRLS ABOUT IT. “YOU CAN ONLY ASK SOMEONE YOU’RE VERY FAMILIAR WITH.”